sibly a variant of   Ashenden   in Kent contexts; note Robt.  <i>Ashinden</i>, 1730 in   IGI   (Deal, Kent)."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. William Ashendon was born in 1410, in Longworth, Berkshire, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with William Ashendon. She died in her hometown."},"et":{"1410–":"1410–Surnud","1410–1450":"1410–1450","1430–1518":"1430–1518","1435–1501":"1435–1501","1410–Female":"1410–Surnud","1501":"1501","1435":"1435","1410":"1410","1 July 1435":"1. juuli 1435","1430":"1430","1450":"1450","1518":"1518","Longworth, Berkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Longworth, Berkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Longworth, Berkshire, England":"Longworth, Berkshire, England"},"fi":{"1410–":"1410–Kuollut","1410–1450":"1410–1450","1430–1518":"1430–1518","1435–1501":"1435–1501","1410–Female":"1410–Kuollut","1501":"1501","1435":"1435","1410":"1410","1 July 1435":"1. heinäkuuta 1435","1430":"1430","1450":"1450","1518":"1518","Longworth, Berkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Longworth, Berkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Longworth, Berkshire, England":"Longworth, Berkshire, England"},"fr":{"1410–":"1410–Décédée","1410–1450":"1410–1450","1430–1518":"1430–1518","1435–1501":"1435